
[1]leucite

   LEU'CITE, n. [Gr. white.] A stony substance, so called from its
   whiteness, found among volcanic productions in Italy, in crystals, or
   in irregular masses; formerly called crystals of white shorl, or white
   granite or granilite.

   Hauy called this mineral, amphigene. It is called by some writers
   leucolite, and by others, dodecahedral zeolite.
